      "PKI (Public Key Infrastructure): framework managing digital certificates and key pairs; CA hierarchy: Root CA (offline, self-signed, signs Intermediate CA certs only) → Intermediate/Issuing CA (online, signs end-entity certs); Certificate Revocation: CRL (Certificate Revocation List — periodic batch download, can be stale) vs OCSP (Online Certificate Status Protocol — real-time per-cert query); OCSP Stapling = server attaches pre-fetched CA-signed OCSP response to TLS handshake, reducing CA load and client latency",
