      "Additional symmetric ciphers: 3DES (EDE: Encrypt-Decrypt-Encrypt with different keys) = 112-bit effective key (2-key) or 168-bit (3-key), deprecated by NIST SP 800-131A after 2023; RC4 = broken stream cipher (WEP exploit — weak key scheduling); ChaCha20-Poly1305 = modern AEAD stream cipher used in TLS 1.3 and WireGuard (software-efficient, no hardware acceleration needed); AES-GCM (Galois/Counter Mode) = AEAD providing encryption + authentication in one pass — most widely deployed secure cipher",
