      "Synthetic/active monitoring vs real user monitoring: Synthetic = scripted transactions simulating user behaviour, detects performance/availability issues proactively; Real User Monitoring (RUM) = observes actual user sessions, identifies real-world performance bottlenecks; both feed into security and operational baselines",
      "Security metrics: Mean Time to Detect (MTTD) = average time to identify an incident; Mean Time to Respond (MTTR) = average time to contain; patch compliance rate; vulnerability closure rate; false positive rate; these are the KPIs reported to management to demonstrate security programme effectiveness",
