      "Red team vs blue team vs purple team: Red team = dedicated adversarial testers simulating real-world threat actors, full attack lifecycle (physical, social engineering, technical), works independently to avoid tipping off blue team; Blue team = defenders using SIEM, EDR, and playbooks; Purple team = NOT a separate team but a collaborative working mode where red and blue coordinate to test detections, validate response, and build new detection rules; Bug bounty = external researcher-driven vulnerability discovery within a defined scope",
